  "articleSummary": "The article argues that \"generative UI\" is not a single technology but a layered stack—product shell, UI composition model, runtime/transport, and agent/tool backend—and that conflating these layers leads to confusion. It maps the current ecosystem (AG-UI, A2UI, json-render, CopilotKit, OpenAI Apps SDK, etc.) onto this framework, then introduces a control spectrum from tool-to-component rendering to open-ended generated HTML, advocating for the minimal agent freedom that solves the user problem. The tone is analytical and educational, using metaphors like \"training wheels\" for chat and \"soup\" for blurred architectures. The intended audience is developers and architects building LLM-powered user interfaces.",
